Citation.sAbstract: Binodal curves of the aqueous N-ethylpyridinium tetrafluoroborate ([EPy]BF4) + Trisodium  citrate (Na3C6H5O7), [EPy]BF4 + Ammonium citrate tribasic ((NH4)3C6H5O7), [EPy]BF4 + Sodium  succinate (Na2C4H4O4) and [EPy]BF4 + Sodium tartrate (Na2C4H4O6) systems have been determined  experimentally at T=298.15K. The Merchuk equation and two other equations were used to correlate  the binodal data. The effective excluded volume (EEV) values obtained from the binodal model for  these four systems were determined. Futhermore, the Othmer-Tobias, Bancroft, two-parameter and  Setschenow-type equations were used for the correlation of the tie-line data. The results show that  good agreement was obtained with the experimental data with two-parameter and Setschenow-type  equotions.
Citation.sTitle: Liquid-Liquid Equilibria of Ionic Liquid N-ethylpyridinium tetrafluoroborate + Trisodium  citrate/Ammonium citrate tribasic/Sodium succinate/Sodium tartrate Aqueous Two-Phase Systems at  298.15K
